  "comb": {
    "aliases": [],
    "text": "In a dream, a comb represents a good man who strives to help, serve,\ncomfort and entertain others. A comb in a dream also represents an auspicious\ntime to be involved in a business partnership or accepting an employment in a\nlarge corporation, since the teeth of a comb are equal. If the teeth of one's comb\nare capped with gold or silver caps, then they represent one's workers. The\ngolden caps represent trustworthy workers and the silver caps represent\ntreacherous and disloyal workers. Combing one's hair in a dream signifies\npaying alms tax, or it could mean distributing charities. A comb in a dream also\ncan be interpreted to denote an honest and a just man, an hour of happiness,\nor a wise person, a judge, a physician, or a preacher one can benefit from his\nknowledge. A comb in a dream also represents a hairdresser or one's mother.\nCombing the hair of an unknown woman in a dream represents a wind that will\nhelp pollinate the trees. In a dream, a comb also represents a sifter or a sieve.\nThe teeth of a comb may represent one's own teeth or the teeth of a saw. It is\nalso said that combing hair in a dream means weaving a carpet. Combing one's\nhair or beard in a dream means dispelling adversities and distress. In a dream,\na comb also represents a good man who is just and equitable with all his friends,\nor it may mean longevity, wealth and victory against one's enemy.",
    "related_entries": [],
    "redirect": null,
    "lookup_aliases": {
      "en": [
        "comb"
      ],
      "fr": [
        "peigne"
      ],
      "ar": [
        "مشط"
      ],
      "tr": [
        "tarak"
      ],
      "de": [
        "kamm"
      ]
    }
  },
