  "olives": {
    "aliases": [
      "Blessed tree"
    ],
    "text": "In a dream, olives represent money, pleasures, or one's\nprosperity. An olive tree in a dream represents a blessed man who benefits his\nfamily, a chaste woman, or it could mean a son who may become a governor. A\nyellow olive in a dream represents heavy concerns about one's religious life. Ifone\npresses olives for oil in a dream, it means that he will earn blessings and benefits.\nIf one sees himself watering an olive tree with olive oil in a dream, it means that\nhe sleeps with his mother. The same interpretation applies if one sees himself\nwatering a garden with vinegar. If one buys an olive tree, or eats from one, or\ndrinks from its oil in a dream, it means blessings, or that he will marry a noble\nand a chaste woman. Seeing the leaves of an olive tree in a dream means following\nthe straight path, or fulfilling one's spiritual obligations, guidance, light, reading\nthe Qur'an, comforting someone's heart, making money for a poor person, except\nif one eats the olive raw in the dream, then it means the opposite, or it implies\npoverty, indebtedness, or it could denote the place, or the direction it comes from.\nThe leaves of an olive tree represent righteous people or spiritual leaders. The\nfruit of an olive tree represents easy money, or living a rich and a happy life.\nSelecting olives or pressing them for oil in a dream means toiling, or hardships.\nAs for a sick person, olives in a dream mean regaining strength and recovering\nfrom his illness. The fruit itself and the leaves also denote assiduousness and\nresoluteness, however, olives in a dream also denote slow growing.",
    "related_entries": [
      "oil"
    ],
    "redirect": null,
    "lookup_aliases": {
      "en": [
        "olives",
        "blessed tree"
      ],
      "fr": [
        "olives"
      ],
      "ar": [
        "زيتون"
      ],
      "tr": [
        "zeytin"
      ],
      "de": [
        "oliven"
      ]
    }
  },
  "omar": {
    "aliases": [],
    "text": "Seeing him in a dream means longevity, trustworthiness and praiseworthy deeds. One who sees him in a dream will speak the truth, be just and call\npeople to the straight path. He also may be able to attend to the Sacred House\nin Mecca in an auxiliary pilgrimage ('Umrah). Ifone shakes hands with Omar bin\nAl-Khattab in a dream, it means that he will prosper and live a pious life, and he\nwill be a vigilant and a strong believer, the value of whose deeds will surpass his\nfame. If one sees him frowning in a dream, it means that Omar is calling for\njustice, commanding what is good and forbidding what is evil. If there is a drought\nin a town and one sees Omar in a dream, it means that rain will fall and be a\nblessing for that land. If there is tyranny in that land and one sees Omar in his\ndream, it means that justice will prevail. If Omar hits someone with a stick, or\nwarns him, or threatens him in a dream, it means that one must renounce the\ncourse of his current actions or deviation from God's path, or perhaps that\nsomeone in authority or a scholar will persecute him. If one sees himself being\nOmar in a dream, or if he wears one of his garments in a dream, it means that\nhe will be awarded honor, a dignified status, or die as a martyr. If one sees Omar\n\nsmiling in a dream, it means that he follows the correct precepts of God's\nMessenger, upon whom be peace, and emulates his practices. Seeing him in a\ndream also means that justice and truth will prevail in his time, or that he is a\ntrustworthy person, or that the propagation of truth is prominent in his time.\nSeeing him in a dream also could mean signing a peace treaty with one's enemy,\nannihilating hatred with love, good luck with one's in-laws, renouncing one's\nattachment to worldly things, though being capable of winning it, or presiding\nover people with justice, love and compassion.",
    "related_entries": [],
    "redirect": null,
    "lookup_aliases": {
      "en": [
        "omar"
      ],
      "fr": [
        "omar"
      ],
      "ar": [
        "عمر"
      ],
      "tr": [
        "ömer"
      ],
      "de": [
        "omar"
      ]
    }
  },
