  "pigeon": {
    "aliases": [
      "Dove",
      "Ringdove",
      "Turtledove"
    ],
    "text": "Seeing a pigeon in a dream means glad\n\ntidings. It is also said that God Almighty will accept the prayers of one who sees\npigeons in his dream. In a dream, a pigeon also represents a trustworthy\nmessenger, a truthful friend, a comforting beloved, a chaste wife, striving to\nsustain one's family, or a fertile woman with a large family. The cooing of\npigeons in a dream means lamentation. Pigeons eggs in a dream represent one's\ndaughters or female neighbors. A domesticated pigeon in a dream represents a\nbeautiful woman from Arabia. Pigeon's nest in a dream represents women's\nparties. Pigeon chicks in a dream represent the boys in a family. Pigeon's\nrumbling or roar in a dream means reproof or censure for a fault. A white pigeon\nin a dream means spirituality, a green pigeon represents piety, while a black\npigeon denotes a mastery. A frightened pigeon in a dream means divorce or\ndeath. A landing pigeon in a dream represents the long awaited arrival of a\nbeloved. Eating pigeon's meat in a dream means to steal money from one's own\nworkers, to defraud them, or to cheat one's servants. Hunting pigeons in a dream\nmeans earning good money from wealthy people. As for an unwed person, seeing\na pigeon inside his house in a dream means marriage. If a pigeon attacks\nsomeone then flies away with him in a dream, it means that happiness and joy\nwill enter his life. However, doves in a dream may represent death. If one sees\nhimself throwing something at a pigeon in a dream, it means that he slanders\na woman, or writes secret correspondence with her. Reaching at a pigeon's nest\nto take its eggs in a dream means taking advantage of a woman, or swindling\nher money. Hunting pigeons in a dream means adultery. Seeing a pigeon\nstanding over one's head, or tied to his neck or shoulders in a dream connotes\none's relationship with his Lord. If in that sense the pigeon is an ugly one, it\nmeans that one's actions are of the same nature. Otherwise, it means the\nopposite. Plucking some feathers from a pigeon in a dream means money.\nSlaughtering a pigeon in a dream means marriage. (Also see Ringdove;\nTurtledove)",
    "related_entries": [],
    "redirect": null,
    "lookup_aliases": {
      "en": [
        "dove",
        "ringdove",
        "pigeon",
        "turtledove"
      ],
      "fr": [
        "pigeon"
      ],
      "ar": [
        "حمامة"
      ],
      "tr": [
        "güvercin"
      ],
      "de": [
        "taube"
      ]
    }
  },
